  • Package coza.opencollab.synthesis.push.dbo

    • Class coza.opencollab.synthesis.push.dbo.Device extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -4157056311695870783L

      • Serialized Fields

        • id

          Long id
          ID for this Device instance.

        • platform

          String platform
          Type for ths Device instance. The device type will be one of the following constants
          • Device.PLATFORM_ANDROID
          • Device.PLATFORM_BLACKBERRY
          • Device.PLATFORM_IOS
          • Device.PLATFORM_WINDOWS

        • regId

          String regId
          Registration ID for push notifications for this Device instance.
          For Android it will be the Registration ID received from GCM.
          For iOS it will be the Device Token received from APNS
          For BlackBerry it will be the BlackBerry PIN (in HEX) retrieved from the device.

        • model

          String model
          The name retrieved from the actual native device.
          On iOS this is the user set name.
          On Android an Blackberry it is the model name of the device

        • username

          String username
          Username of the person to who this native device belongs

        • uuid

          String uuid
          Unique identifier for the native device.

        • postedTimestamp

          Timestamp postedTimestamp
          The timestamp of the last update for this Device details.

        • versionNumber

          Long versionNumber
          Version number for this Device record

        • tuples

          Set<E> tuples

        • preferences

          Set<E> preferences

    • Class coza.opencollab.synthesis.push.dbo.Preference extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -8566828971044365068L

      • Serialized Fields

        • id

          Long id
          ID for this Preference instance.

        • device

          Device device
          Device this preference is linked too

        • enabled

          boolean enabled
          Enabled denotes whether the whether the user wants to receive Push from a given module. If an entry does not exist in the table the user should not receive a notification

        • sender

          String sender
          Id of the sender of the message. The sender can be a module, a tool, or any level implemented

        • postedTimestamp

          Timestamp postedTimestamp
          PostedTimestamp at which the preference was set and inserted into the database.

        • versionNumber

          Long versionNumber
          VersionNumber is the versionNumber of the preference.
